        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-19T00:15:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve been using %q for short strings and %s for paths and URLs. I don\u0027t like how \"https://chromium-swarm-dev.appspot.com\" looks. It doesn\u0027t seem to need to be quoted since URL semantics make it somewhat obvious where the URL begins and ends, so I\u0027ve been using \": \" as a delimiter for them.\n\nSee, for example, create above:\n\"creating instance %q\", hostname -\u003e \"creating instance \u0027whatever\u0027\"\n\"created instance: %s\", URL -\u003e \"created instance: https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/p/zones/z/instances/whatever\"",
      "parentUuid": "a06c41c8_492dc7a8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 226,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 226,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "f32a785aec3c39b84ea81fa9bfbb7fb1c3c34d66",
