    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ca1a91b6_12345003",
        "filename": "gce/appengine/frontend/queue.yaml",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 18,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-17T16:56:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "writing comment here, but it applies to overall CL design:\n\nSo, if we have just 6k machines, this queue will be 100% busy and we\u0027d be re-querying each machine every ~60 seconds, and swarming will be serving sustained 100 QPS.\n\nHence, should we bother to reduce load on swarming?\n\nIf yes, then \n\n1) we could insert task queue tasks with delay of M minutes and include timestamp in task id for deduplication:\n  task_id \u003d {vm}-{timestamp-rounded-to-M-minutes}\n  payload {vm}\nthis way we ensure that each VM is queried every ~M minutes.\n\n2) would swarming benefit from batch requests for bot status?\n\n\nAdditionally, can we complement this with pubsub from swarming wrt to change of bot status?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 18,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 18,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "f32a785aec3c39b84ea81fa9bfbb7fb1c3c34d66",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "619bc8ff_12bf025b",
        "filename": "gce/appengine/frontend/queue.yaml",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 18,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-19T00:15:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think Swarming can handle the load, given that each of its bots is polling every minute anyways (same frequency as the cron job which launches these task queues). If we want to reduce load, we can trivially just adjust the cron to be every 5 minutes or every 10 minutes, can\u0027t we? Do we need the timestamp semantics you propose?\n\nI\u0027d rather not use pub/sub, it\u0027s been catastrophically bad in the past because retransmission semantics are ill-defined (e.g. message that is pulled but not acked will be resent, but when?). See https://crbug.com/626501 and https://crbug.com/709284 for some background.",
      "parentUuid": "ca1a91b6_12345003",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 18,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 18,
        "endChar": 13
      },
